Itoa

Function Itoa(n):
    If n is 0:
        Return "0"
    
    Initialize result as an empty string
    Initialize isNegative as false
    
    If n is less than 0:
        Set isNegative to true
        Set n to -n (work with the absolute value of n)
    
    While n is greater than 0:
        Set digit to n mod 10  // Get the last digit of n
        Convert digit to a character by adding '0' to digit
        Prepend the character to the result string
        Set n to n divided by 10  // Remove the last digit from n
    
    If isNegative is true:
        Prepend "-" to the result string
    
    Return result
